# Timelogs

The Timelogs page (`/timelogs`) lets employees record and review their working hours on a per-day basis, organised by ISO week (Monday–Sunday). Admins, owners and managers can additionally inspect any employee's timelog history.

---

## Route

`/timelogs` — protected route, accessible to **employees only** (users with an employee record). Users without an employee record are redirected to the home page.

Managers, Owners, and Admins review and approve timelog entries via the **Approvals** page (`/management/approvals`).

---

## Behaviour by Role

### Employees

- The page loads automatically scoped to the logged-in user's employee record (resolved via `GET /employees/me`).
- No employee selector is shown.
- The week is rendered as a 7-row **inline-editable** grid (`EmployeeWeekGrid`). Each row represents one day.
- Hours, type and description are editable directly in the cell for rows that are not `submitted` or `approved`.
- A **Save** button appears in the pinned right column only for rows that have unsaved local edits.
- On save, the row is created (`POST /timelogs`) or updated (`PUT /timelogs/:id`) depending on whether a record already exists for that day.
- A weekly total badge is shown at the top of the editable grid.

### Admins / Owners / Managers

- An **Employee** dropdown is shown above the week navigator.
- Until an employee is selected the grid area displays a prompt.
- The employee list is fetched from `GET /employees`.
- A **read-only** AG Grid is rendered using `Timelogs.columns.tsx` showing full timelog detail for the selected employee and week.
- A weekly total badge appears in the page header once an employee is selected.

---

## Week Navigation

- Defaults to the current ISO week on mount.
- **Previous / Next** arrow buttons shift the displayed week by one week.
- A **Today** button appears when the current week is not selected, and jumps back to the current week.
- The selected range is displayed as `MMM D – MMM D, YYYY` (e.g. `Mar 9 – Mar 15, 2026`).

---

## Data Fetching

- Hook: `useTimelogsByEmployeeAndWeek(employeeId, startDate, endDate)` from `useTimelog.tsx`.
- API call: `GET /timelogs/employee/:id?startDate=YYYY-MM-DD&endDate=YYYY-MM-DD`.
- The query is disabled until an `effectiveEmployeeId` is resolved.
- Data is re-fetched automatically whenever the week or the selected employee changes.
- In the employee editable grid, server data is merged into local row state as it arrives; dirty (unsaved) rows preserve their local edits and only sync `id` and `status` from the server response.

---

## Grid — Employee view (`EmployeeWeekGrid`)

Inline-editable 7-row grid, one row per day of the week. Column definitions are defined inline in `EmployeeWeekGrid`.

| Column      | Field         | Editable | Notes                                                |
| ----------- | ------------- | -------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| Day         | `dayLabel`    | No       | Formatted `ddd, MMM D`; pinned left                  |
| Hours       | `totalHours`  | Yes      | Number cell editor; 0–24; displays as `Xh`           |
| Type        | `type`        | Yes      | Select editor; colour-coded badge                    |
| Description | `description` | Yes      | Free text                                            |
| Status      | `status`      | No       | Colour-coded badge; `–` if no record                 |
| _(save)_    | `isDirty`     | No       | Save button appears only on dirty rows; pinned right |

Rows with status `submitted` or `approved` are not editable.

---

## Grid — Privileged view (read-only)

Rendered with **AG Grid** via the shared `DataGrid` component. Column definitions and the default column def are exported from `Timelogs.columns.tsx`.

| Column            | Field            | Notes                                               |
| ----------------- | ---------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| Date              | `date`           | Formatted `ddd, MMM DD`; pinned left                |
| Employee          | `employeeName`   | Hidden when a specific employee is already selected |
| Company / Project | `companyName`    | Falls back to `–`                                   |
| Hours             | `totalHours`     | Numeric; displayed as `Xh`                          |
| Type              | `type`           | Colour-coded badge (see below)                      |
| Status            | `status`         | Colour-coded badge (see below)                      |
| Description       | `description`    | Flexible width; tooltip on overflow                 |
| Location          | `location`       | Shows `Remote` when `isRemote` is true              |
| Billable          | `billable`       | Shows calculated value `billableHours × hourlyRate` |
| Approved By       | `approvedByName` | Falls back to `–`                                   |

All columns are sortable, filterable and resizable by default.

### Type badge colours

| Value      | Colour |
| ---------- | ------ |
| `standard` | Blue   |
| `overtime` | Orange |
| `holiday`  | Teal   |
| `sick`     | Red    |
| `other`    | Gray   |

### Status badge colours

| Value       | Colour |
| ----------- | ------ |
| `draft`     | Gray   |
| `submitted` | Blue   |
| `approved`  | Green  |
| `rejected`  | Red    |

---

## File Structure

```
Timelogs/
├── Timelogs.tsx          # Page component + EmployeeWeekGrid sub-component
├── Timelogs.columns.tsx  # AG Grid column definitions for the privileged read-only view
├── constants/
│   └── index.ts          # TYPE_OPTIONS select data, STATUS_COLORS map
├── types/
│   └── index.ts          # WeekRow local state type
├── Modals/               # Empty — create/edit modal not yet implemented
└── README
```

---

## Planned Enhancements

- **Create modal** — open a form modal (`Modals/CreateTimelogModal.tsx`) to create a timelog for a specific day without inline editing.
- **Submit workflow** — a "Submit week" button in the employee view to bulk-set all draft timelogs to `submitted` for manager review (server endpoint `POST /timelogs/bulk/submit` already exists).
- **Owner employee filter** — scope the employee dropdown to only employees belonging to the owner's companies.
- Manager approval is handled separately on the **Approvals** page (`/management/approvals`).
